```class Solution {
    public int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) {
        int res = 0;
        while (target > startValue) {
            target++;
            res++;
        }
        return res + (startValue - target);
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(target))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The algorithm uses a while loop to increment the target until it is greater than or equal to the startValue. This is done to minimize the number of operations needed. Then, it calculates the remaining operations needed to reach the target from the startValue.

